<h2 style = "text-align:center; font-family:Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">About</h2>

<div class ="about">
<p>Hi! My name is Addie, and I love to bake cake, cookies, muffins, etc. Below you'll find one of my favorite recipes: banana bread! It's easy to make and very delicious.</p>
</div>
<br>

<h3 id = "h3">Banana Bread Recipe</h3>
<div id="recipe">
<p>Prep Time: 10 minutes</p>
<p>Bake Time: 35 minutes</p>
</div>

<p style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-weight: bold;">Ingredients</p>
<ul id="ingredients">
    <li>1/4 cup melted butter</li>
    <li>1/4 cup unsweetened applesauce</li>
    <li>2 eggs</li>
    <li>1/2 cup white sugar</li>
    <li>1/4 cup light brown sugar</li>
    <li>1 and 1/2 cup all purpose flour</li>
    <li>1 tsp. baking soda</li>
    <li>3 medium overripe bananas</li>
    <li>1 tsp vanilla</li>
    <li>chocolate chips (optional)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>


<p style="font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;font-weight:bold;">Directions</p>
<ol id ="directions">
    <li>Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.</li>
    <li>In a bowl, mix together the dry ingredients.</li>
    <li>In a separate bowl mix together the wet ingredients.</li>
    <ul>
        <li>Mash the banana first.</li>
        <li>Then add the eggs, applesauce, and vanilla.</li>
    </ul>
    <li>Mix the wet and dry ingredients together. Stir slowly with a wisk until combined.</li>
    <li>Add chocolate chips if desired.</li>
    <li>Pour the batter into a greased bread pan (or muffin tins work too). Bake at 350 for 35 minutes.</li>
    <li>Let cool and then enjoy!</li>
</ol>
<br>
